#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:82
msgid "Setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:84
msgid "Install Node.js [v22.16.0](https://nodejs.org/en/download) then run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:86
#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:99
msgid "moon pilot\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:91
msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:93
msgid ""
"MoonBit Pilot will automatically use the first model in your "
"configuration file (in this case, \"sonnet4\"). You can configure "
"multiple models and they can be specified by `--model` parameter when you"
" start MoonBit Pilot."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:95
msgid "Interactive Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:97
msgid "Start interactive mode using the first model specified in preview section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:104
msgid "Or specify a particular model:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:106
msgid "moon pilot --model k2\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:111
msgid "Interactive Commands"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:113
msgid ""
"Once in interactive mode, you can input your requirements normally and "
"MoonBit Pilot will respond and execute tasks for you."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:115
msgid "act ▶ what does this project do?\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:119
msgid "Exiting Interactive Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:121
msgid "Use `:exit` or `Ctrl+D` to exit the application"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:122
msgid "Use `Ctrl+C` to stop the current request and clear the current input"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:126
msgid "Print/Non-Interactive Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:128
msgid ""
"You can execute one-time commands through the `-p` flag. Non-interactive "
"mode supports piping:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:130
msgid "echo \"What does this project do\" | moon pilot -p\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:133
msgid ""
"This command will automatically exit after completion, making it perfect "
"for programmatic calls (through subprocess forking in programming "
"languages or shell script invocation)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:135
msgid "You can also use it with `cat`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:137
msgid "cat prompt.md | moon pilot -p\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:141
msgid ""
"Additionally, non-interactive mode also has session concepts. The "
"previous commands each create a new session, which can be simply "
"understood as stateless."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:143
msgid ""
"You can view recently executed non-interactive commands through "
"`conversations`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:145
msgid "moon pilot conversations\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:149
msgid ""
"1. 0ada20c9\n"
"   Name: Session 7/18/2025, 2:30:40 PM\n"
"   Description: Interactive conversation\n"
"   Messages: 0\n"
"   Created: 7/18/2025, 2:30:40 PM\n"
"   Updated: 7/18/2025, 2:30:40 PM\n"
"\n"
"2. e1a5b071\n"
"   Name: Session 7/17/2025, 11:55:38 AM\n"
"   Description: Interactive conversation\n"
"   Messages: 18\n"
"   Created: 7/17/2025, 11:55:38 AM\n"
"   Updated: 7/17/2025, 11:56:32 AM\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:166
msgid "You can view details through session ID:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:168
msgid "moon pilot conversation 0ada20c9\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:172
msgid "or you can export the conversation to makrdown file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:174
msgid "moon pilot conversation 0ada20c9 --output conversation.md\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:178
msgid ""
"If you want to continue from the last command execution, allowing this "
"modification to have the context from the previous time, you can use "
"`--continue` to continue the last session. This way, both commands will "
"share the same conversation list:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:180
msgid "echo \"What did I ask you before?\" | moon pilot -p --continue\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:184
msgid ""
"This allows you to complete conversations through multiple `moon pilot` "
"calls. This means any third-party application can easily integrate with "
"`moon pilot` through simple command-line calls. In the future, we can "
"also provide SDKs for various languages, making it convenient for other "
"languages to use `moon pilot` to create interactive interfaces and "
"implement package migration work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:186
msgid ""
"Of course, you can also resume to a specific session using the `--resume`"
" parameter, which will switch to that session:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:188
msgid "echo \"What did I ask you before?\" | moon pilot -p --resume ed19c993\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/getting-started.md:192
msgid "This provides excellent controllability."
msgstr ""

